At least four people have been killed in intensifying airstrikes on Idlib, the last rebel bastion in Syria. Reports indicate that families in war-torn Syria are making improvised gas masks in fear of a chemical attack. Journalist Azhar Vadi, who is in Turkey at the border with Syria, says the attacks are mostly affecting the rural areas. “We based on the border between Syria and Turkey which is about 20 or 30 kilometres from Idlib city. The main attacks right now by the Syrian air force and the Russian air force has been on the border between the province itself and the Syrian military controlled areas. The attacks have mainly been in the rural areas and the attempts by the Syrian military and Russian forces, is to retake two highways that link the south of the country to the north”.